day for the queen/king
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number: 1
Definition:[mustering] a day when musterers elect not to work or are unable to work but remain on full pay.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
Citations
Date: 0/0/1947
Source: Straggle Muster
Author: NEWTON
Vol / Page: 119
Edition:
Quote: A foggy day is usually a cause for rejoicing by a musterer, for as it is impossible for him to see to do his work, he and his dogs have a day off - in musterers' parlance, 'a day for a king.'
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1949
